To fix this, we should make sure that before using topOffsetHistoryPos as an index, we first check that it???s in the valid range. Basically, we???d want to confirm it???s not less than zero and not past the end of the array before using it. Here???s a snippet showing how the check could look:

```
if (topOffsetHistoryPos >= 0 && topOffsetHistoryPos < topOffsetHistory.size()) {
    refreshDisasm(topOffsetHistory[topOffsetHistoryPos]);
}
```
With this in place, if a user tries to undo at the very beginning of the seek history, nothing should happen, and the app will remain stable. It might also be a good idea to disable or gray out the undo UI button when users can???t go back any further, just to make it clear.

